In this article, President Trump announces his nomination of Judge Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court. He praises Barrett's qualifications and character, highlighting her achievements as a legal scholar and her commitment to following the Constitution. Trump urges the Senate to provide a fair and timely confirmation process, emphasizing the importance of the Supreme Court's rulings on issues such as the Second Amendment, religious liberty, and public safety. Barrett expresses her gratitude and pledges to serve to the best of her ability if confirmed. She also acknowledges the legacy of Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg and the influence of her mentor, Justice Antonin Scalia. Barrett emphasizes her commitment to impartiality and serving the American people. The article concludes with Trump thanking those in attendance and expressing confidence in Barrett's confirmation.